    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>Now it is more like \"get ALL the offsets first, then get values one by one and put them on their places\".</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That is probably <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loop-invariant_code_motion\">LICM</a> moving the address calculation out of the loop.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If I grow that const/const/store chain to be long enough to run out of free registers, offsets are spilled to the stack.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think regalloc doesn't implement <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rematerialization\">rematerialization</a> for the address computation. <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"254389\">@Chris Fallin</span> is that right?</p>",
        "id": 293571248,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1660581648
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yep, I've noticed this inefficiency too; I've addressed it as part of the mid-end optimizer I'm working on now, which does GVN + LICM + remat in a unified way</p>",
